        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 12:05AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 1205 AM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Mountain Springs to Cross Keys to near Skipperton, and
moving northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Macon, Gray, Payne, Payne City, Postell, James, Rutland, Mountain
Springs, Griswoldville, Haddock, Greenberry Crossroads, Cross Keys,
Wesleyan, Skipperton, and Arkwright.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
